This course is meant for both students of literature studies as well as students from other fields who are interested in Japanese literature. The lectures give an overview of Japanese literary history from first texts and classical era literature up until the works of contemporary authors; the seminars require the reading of central works of japanese literature and they are then discussed in smaller groups. In order to pass, in addition to taking part in the seminars, students must take quizes in the courses page in Moodle e-study platform.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the central literary works, authors and genres of Japanese literature from the Classical Era (794 CE) until today in their historical and cultural context and make connections to similar developments in Western litarature and culture.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. students are able to name and characterize  the central literary works, authors and genres of Japanese literature from the Classical Era until today. 2. students are able to analyze a literary work central to Japanese literature and take into account its context (time of writing, the rest of the authors works, Japanese culture etc) 3. students are able to connect developments in Japanese literature with similar developments in Western literatures (ie French or German literature). 4. students value Japanese literature as one comparable to Western literatures (ie French or German literature)
